Case No. 6,617. HINE v. WAHL. [Decree by GRESHAM. District Judge, sustaining the validity of reissued letters patent No. 4,372 of patent No. 73.425. This patent was granted January 14, 1868, to N. W. Green, •and was reissued May 9, 1871. No opinion delivered. Decree reported in 4 Trans. Rec. 1882, p. 321G, clerk’s office United States supreme court, and affirmed by divided supreme •court, without opinions, December 18. 1882.] [Cited in Green v. French, 11 Fed. 591, and Andrews v. Eames, 15 Fed. 110. For other cases involving the same patent, see note to Andrews v. Denslow, Case No. 372.]
